                        <h3 class="py-3"> <strong> Car Insurance</strong></h3>
                    <p>Car Insurance is a contract between the insurance company and insured that safeguards the policyholder against financial loss in case of theft or accident. A car insurance policy also offers coverage for damage or loss caused to your car.</p>
                    <p><img style="margin: 10px; float: right;" src="https://www.policybazaar.com/images/Health/car-insurance-types.jpg" alt="Car Insurance Types" width="380" height="480" /></p>
                    <p>It is mandatory to buy car insurance in India irrespective of the vehicle type, i.e. personal or commercial vehicle. Moreover, the premium amount of your car insurance is decided based on the Insured Declared Value or IDV of the vehicle. If you increase the IDV, the premium rises and if you lower it, the premium reduces.</p>
                    <p>It is important for any policyholder to compare various car insurance options before going for car insurance renewal or buying a new policy. Compare various insurance plans online on Policybazaar and buy the one that fulfills your insurance expectations hassle-free:</p>
